article.headline: Texas State 77, Texas-San Antonio 65
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Chris Agwumaro scored 19 points and grabbed four rebounds to lead Texas State to a 77-65 win over Texas-San Antonio on Saturday night. Brandon Bush, Dylan Moseley and Brent Holder had six rebounds apiece for the Bobcats (9-17, 4-9 Southland). Texas State held a 41-34 rebounding edge over the Roadrunners (6-19, 2-10). Andrew Francis led Texas-San Antonio with 13 points, seven rebounds and four blocks. Agwumaro made 9-of-10 free throws. Also scoring in double figures for Texas State were Antwoine Blanchard with 12 points, and Bush and Holder with 11 points each. Texas State trailed by five at the half but outscored the Roadrunners 47-30 after the break. Kurt Attaway finished with 12 points and five assists, while Ryan Williams came off the bench to score 11 points and grab seven rebounds. Isaiah Allen added 10 points and four rebounds.
